## Data Flow Legend

| Arrow Type | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `<-->` | Bi-directional communication |
| `-->` | One-directional (platform initiates) |
| `Bi-directional Sync` | Real-time sync both directions |
| `Webhooks` | Third-party pushes data to platform |
| `API` | Platform calls third-party API |
| `OAuth2` | User-authorized integration |

## Integration Categories

### 1. Core Infrastructure (Required for MVP)
- **PostgreSQL**: Primary data store
- **Redis**: Caching, queues, sessions
- **Cloudflare R2**: Media storage
- **OpenAI**: AI processing (chatbot, content)
- **HubSpot**: CRM and lead management
- **Twilio**: Messaging alerts
- **SendGrid**: Email campaigns

### 2. Growth Phase (Post-MVP)
- **Bland.ai/Vapi**: AI voice qualification
- **HeyGen**: AI video generation
- **Buffer**: Social media scheduling
- **Google Calendar**: Appointment booking
- **Google Analytics 4**: Analytics and attribution

### 3. SaaS Multi-Tenant (Phase 2)
- All integrations support per-tenant API keys
- OAuth2 for user-authorized access
- Per-tenant usage tracking and billing

## Integration Priority

| Priority | Integration | Sprint |
|---|---|---|
| P0 (Critical) | OpenAI, PostgreSQL, Redis, R2 | Sprint 0-1 |
| P0 (Critical) | HubSpot, SendGrid, Twilio | Sprint 2 |
| P1 (High) | Google Calendar, Bland.ai/Vapi | Sprint 3 |
| P1 (High) | HeyGen, Buffer | Sprint 4 |
| P2 (Medium) | Google Analytics 4 | Sprint 5 |
